u7684\u7684\u7684\u7684\u7684\u7684"}, {"v": 5, "s": 1, "text": "Okay, let's try to figure out this problem. So, the farmer has three items: a fox, a chicken, and a bag of grain. He needs to cross a river using a boat that can carry him and one item at a time. The problem is that if he leaves alone, the fox will eat the chicken, and the chicken will eat the grain. So, how can the farmer get everything across safely\uff1f\n\nAlright, let's break down the problem step by step.\n\nFirst, the farmer needs to take the boat across the river. The boat can carry him and one item at\u4e00\u6b21\u3002 So,\u6bcf\u6b21 crossing,\u4ed6 can take either the fox, the chicken, or the grain, or\u4ed6 himself\u3002 But, if he leaves alone, then the fox or chicken will eat the other items\u3002 So, the main challenge is to ensure that all three items (fox, chicken, grain) are safely across without any being eaten\u3002\n\nLet's think about possible solutions.\n\nOption 1: Take the fox first. Then, the farmer takes the fox across, and leaves the chicken and grain behind\u3002 But, when he returns back to get the chicken and grain across, the fox might eat the chicken or grain if left alone\u3002 This seems risky because if the farmer leaves the chicken and grain, then the fox could eat them\u3002 So, this might not be safe\u3002\n\nOption 2\uff1a Take the chicken first\u3002 Then, the farmer takes the chicken across, and leaves the fox and"}, {"v": 6, "s": 1, "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n