 this down. First, the boat can carry the farmer and one item at a time. So,\u6bcf\u6b21\u8fc7\u6cb3\uff0c the farmer can take either the fox, the chicken,\u6216\u8005 the grain, but\u4e0d\u80fd take more than one item\u3002 \n\nSo, the farmer needs to decide which item to take each time\u3002  But,\u5982\u679c he takes the fox, then the chicken will be eaten by the fox\u3002 Similarly,\u5982\u679c he takes the chicken, then the fox will be eaten by the chicken\uff1f And\u5982\u679c he takes the grain, then the chicken or fox will not eat it\uff1f \n\nWait,\u6240\u4ee5 the farmer needs to find a way to get all three items across safely\u3002 \n\nLet's think about possible strategies. \n\nOption 1: Take the fox first\u3002 Then, leave the chicken and grain on the other side\u3002 But,\u5982\u679c the fox eats the chicken, then the farmer needs to bring the chicken and grain back, but this would require the farmer to cross again, which may be possible\uff1f \n\nBut, this seems like a"}, {"v": 6, "s": 2, "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n